{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"I am not sure this is a great idea.  This makes the light distance parameter behave non-continuously.  As you make the distance smaller eventually it just jumps to be huge.  I would suggest a more natural parameterization would be to set the light.distance to infinity if you do not want the cutoff to occur.  We already set some things like an empty box to infinity values.  Light.distance = 0 should probably make the light not emit anything.  This way the parameterization is continuous and logical, otherwise 0 is a magic value, which is always problematic to explain and import\/export.\r\n\r\nI'm just thinking from a new user perspective.","created_at":"2018-09-25T13:42:21.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14962#issuecomment-424348127","id":424348127,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14962","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQyNDM0ODEyNw==","updated_at":"2018-09-25T13:42:21.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/424348127","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/588541?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/bhouston","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU4ODU0MQ==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"bhouston","type":"User","id":588541,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Actually I'm fine with this change.  I'm over thinking it.","created_at":"2018-09-25T13:43:24.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14962#issuecomment-424348501","id":424348501,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14962","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQyNDM0ODUwMQ==","updated_at":"2018-09-25T13:43:24.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/424348501","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/588541?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/bhouston","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU4ODU0MQ==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"bhouston","type":"User","id":588541,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Thanks!\r\n\r\n>  As you make the distance smaller eventually it just jumps to be huge.\r\n\r\nThis is the case already \u2014 when `distance` reaches 0, `decay` is internally set to 0 and all attenuation is turned off. With this change (in physically-correct mode), `distance` reaching 0 causes the cutoff to be removed, while attenuation continues to apply unless `decay` is manually set to 0. I think this is clearer \u2014 `distance=0` is a magical value in both cases, but now it only affects the range of the light. Infinity would also be fine with me, but requires some adjustments.\r\n\r\nBut I should note that although I ran into this while testing glTF's `KHR_lights_punctual` (see #14927), this fix is not strictly required to implement the extension. The alternative would be for GLTFLoader to choose some arbitrarily large float for the `distance`, when a light does not provide a cutoff range.","created_at":"2018-09-25T16:00:26.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14962#issuecomment-424402367","id":424402367,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14962","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQyNDQwMjM2Nw==","updated_at":"2018-09-25T16:00:38.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/424402367","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1848368?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/donmccurdy","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE4NDgzNjg=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"donmccurdy","type":"User","id":1848368,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"> I would suggest a more natural parameterization would be to set the light.distance to infinity if you do not want the cutoff to occur.\r\n\r\nThat would definitely be ideal.\r\n\r\nFor context, we went with `0` originally because of serialisation. JSON doesn't support `Infinity` \ud83d\ude15","created_at":"2018-09-25T16:23:58.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14962#issuecomment-424410686","id":424410686,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14962","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQyNDQxMDY4Ng==","updated_at":"2018-09-25T16:53:33.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/424410686","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"Should light be attenuated if distance is 0 in physically correct mode?","created_at":"2018-09-25T18:04:19.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14962#issuecomment-424443812","id":424443812,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14962","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQyNDQ0MzgxMg==","updated_at":"2018-09-25T18:04:19.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/424443812","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"Hmm, I guess for physical mode that's a good default.","created_at":"2018-09-25T18:05:43.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14962#issuecomment-424444285","id":424444285,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14962","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQyNDQ0NDI4NQ==","updated_at":"2018-09-25T18:05:43.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/424444285","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"Thanks!","created_at":"2018-09-25T18:06:03.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14962#issuecomment-424444390","id":424444390,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14962","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQyNDQ0NDM5MA==","updated_at":"2018-09-25T18:06:03.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/424444390","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Ideally there would be no value of distance that affects attenuation, except to impose a cutoff. Then attenuation is purely a function of decay and it feels simpler. So this PR handles that. But whether distance=0 should mean \"infinite\" or \"no light\", I could go either way... does seem a bit more complex to use `Infinity`, but it would be very clear.","created_at":"2018-09-25T18:20:39.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14962#issuecomment-424449150","id":424449150,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14962","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQyNDQ0OTE1MA==","updated_at":"2018-09-25T18:20:39.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/424449150","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1848368?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/donmccurdy","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE4NDgzNjg=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"donmccurdy","type":"User","id":1848368,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/orgs"}},{"index":8,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"I hadn't intended for this change to affect scenes not using physically-correct mode, but [Twitter user \\@trs_torosalmon has pointed out](https:\/\/twitter.com\/trs_torosalmon\/status\/1046241992429064192) that it can \u2014\r\n\r\n| case | consistent |\r\n|----|----|\r\n| distance=0, decay=0 | \u2705 |\r\n| distance=0, decay>0 | \u2705 |\r\n| distance>0, decay>0 | \u2705 |\r\n| distance>0, decay=0 | \u274c |\r\n\r\nIn the last case, `distance>0, decay=0`,\r\n\r\n- Before: Light has no attenuation and no distance cutoff.\r\n- After: Light has no attenuation within the distance cutoff, but falls to 0 outside of that.\r\n\r\nThe relevant GLSL:\r\n\r\n```glsl\r\nif( cutoffDistance > 0.0 ) {\r\n\r\n  return pow( saturate( -lightDistance \/ cutoffDistance + 1.0 ), decayExponent );\r\n\r\n}\r\n\r\nreturn 1.0;\r\n```\r\n\r\nI assumed that `pow( 0, 0 )` would be `1.0`, as in scripting languages. [That isn't the case](https:\/\/www.khronos.org\/registry\/OpenGL-Refpages\/gl4\/html\/pow.xhtml):\r\n\r\n> <img width=\"911\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-10-02 at 8 21 03 am\" src=\"https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/1848368\/46358767-91a9ac00-c61c-11e8-80e8-4702e11920a7.png\">\r\n\r\nWe can fix this by adding another check, `decayExponent > 0`, to the conditional. Alternatively we could keep it: arguably the new behavior is more consistent with what the user has written, although I don't love the idea of relying on that `pow()` nuance.","created_at":"2018-10-02T15:32:11.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14962#issuecomment-426319550","id":426319550,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14962","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQyNjMxOTU1MA==","updated_at":"2018-10-02T15:32:23.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/426319550","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1848368?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/donmccurdy","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE4NDgzNjg=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"donmccurdy","type":"User","id":1848368,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/orgs"}},{"index":9,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Oops, I assumed `pow( 0, 0 )` will be one, too. I prefer adding `decayExponent > 0`, and this fix should be in r97 unless it's too late.","created_at":"2018-10-02T15:39:42.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14962#issuecomment-426322366","id":426322366,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14962","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQyNjMyMjM2Ng==","updated_at":"2018-10-02T15:48:07.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/426322366","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/takahirox\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/takahirox\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/7637832?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/takahirox","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/takahirox\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/takahirox","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/takahirox\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc2Mzc4MzI=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/takahirox\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/takahirox\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/takahirox\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"takahirox","type":"User","id":7637832,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/takahirox\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/takahirox\/orgs"}},{"index":10,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"@donmccurdy Sounds good to me \ud83d\udc4d\r\n\r\n```js\r\nif( cutoffDistance > 0.0 && decayExponent > 0.0 ) {\r\n```\r\n\r\n","created_at":"2018-10-09T22:29:50.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14962#issuecomment-428375252","id":428375252,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14962","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQyODM3NTI1Mg==","updated_at":"2018-10-09T22:29:50.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/428375252","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}}]}